SIMPLE: ruinous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ruinous
<hw>Ru"in*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ruinosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ruineux</ets>. See
<er>Ruin</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Causing, or tending to cause,
ruin; destructive; baneful; pernicious; <as>as, a <ex>ruinous</ex>
project</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>After a night of storm so <qex>ruinous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by ruin; ruined; dilapidated; <as>as,
an edifice, bridge, or wall in a <ex>ruinous</ex> state</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Composed of, or consisting in, ruins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behold, Damascus . . . shall be a <qex>ruinous</qex> heap.</q>
<rj><qau>Isa. xvii. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Dilapidated; decayed; demolished; pernicious;
destructive; baneful; wasteful; mischievous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ru"in*ous*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ru"in*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rukh</ent>⟦br⟧
